author: codex
acceptance_criteria: Projects v2 commands expose intuitive SDK command contracts; project item provenance survives pm tag normalization; push/pull status mapping is symmetric; existing tags are preserved during import updates; dry-run and add-missing safety semantics are tested; full release check passes; real authenticated read-only validation is recorded; no secrets or private data are tracked.
definition_of_ready: Existing feat/projects-v2-sync implementation and follow-up hardening are present; gh authentication is available; mutations use dry-run or isolated test data unless explicitly safe.
value: Agents can use GitHub Projects as a shared planning surface without losing pm context or corrupting status/provenance.
impact: Adds production-grade multi-surface project context synchronization for pm-managed work.
outcome: "Deterministic, tested, agent-friendly Projects v2 workflows with safe bidirectional mapping."
why_now: The implementation is already in progress and must be completed before the branch can be reviewed and released.
risk: high
confidence: medium
resolution: "Implemented and verified Projects v2 bidirectional sync with status symmetry, tag-preserving imports, redirect credential isolation, and real CLI/API dry-run validation."
expected_result: Projects commands are discoverable and safe by default; status/provenance round trips preserve data; release checks pass.
actual_result: All nine package actions activated; 78 tests and release gate passed; authenticated list/fields/dry-run succeeded; no current vulnerabilities.
comments[4]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-11T18:03:54.172Z",codex,"Initial verification: git diff --check clean; npm test passed 78/78; npm run release:check passed including zero production vulnerabilities and changelog check."
  "2026-07-11T18:05:09.310Z",codex,"Real-life SDK/CLI verification with pm 2026.7.11: local package install activated all nine command/action paths with health ok; read-only project list found unbraind/1; fields returned 18 fields and five Status options; default sync dry-run produced a push/pull plan without remote writes. GitHub security review: only alert is fixed CVE-2026-54285 in a dev transitive dependency; npm audit reports zero vulnerabilities."
  "2026-07-11T18:12:05.139Z",codex,"Sourcery review remediation: removed ad-hoc _pmRoot mutation and hard-coded tracker fallback by passing ctx.pm_root explicitly into applyPushEntry; normalized README terminology to Projects v2. Full release gate rerun after changes."
  "2026-07-11T18:13:43.561Z",codex,"Greptile/Gemini round-two remediation: dry-run import now reads the local store for idempotent create/update planning; GraphQL fails early with token guidance; nullable project/item/field nodes are filtered or normalized; sync token requirement is explicit; malformed non-string provenance tags are safely rejected with regression coverage. Full release gate passes with 79 tests."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-11T18:03:54.172Z",codex,Existing uncommitted edits were present at session start and are preserved; pm-cli itself remains read-only.
learnings[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-11T18:03:54.172Z",codex,"pm normalizes tags to lowercase, so case-sensitive GitHub node IDs require a reversible lowercase-safe provenance encoding."
  "2026-07-11T18:05:09.811Z",codex,A repo-local local-source install is necessary to test newly registered nested extension commands; invoking the globally/previously installed extension correctly rejected the new path before activation.
